history.text: I thought Tom Hanks as Woody was so good in Toy Story! What did you think?
I liked Tim allen more.
Why did you like Woody.
I tend to like cowboys. I agree that Tim Allen as Buzz Lightyear was also a great casting decison.
What did you think about that scene where Buzz realizes he's a toy?
I suppose the juxtaposition of the two is what made it work.
I don't recall that scene, to be honest.
He's sitting on a landing and when the camera pans out you see him realizing that he's just a little toy.
I'm not sure about that, sorry.
Did you agree with the critics?
I totally agree that it's a work of genius.
Yeah, it's pretty crazy what pixar can make interesting.
It get's 100% on rotten tomatoes which is not easy to do

Yeah, I was wondering about that as well. Even the most revered
 moved don't do that.
What did you think about when andy first got buzz?
I was immediately worried about how Woody would react. Funny how the movie makes us anthropomorphize toys.
I think it does the anthropomorphizing for us.
Definitely. Who was your favorite secondary character? I enjoyed Mr. Potato Head. He's such a character.
Actually mr. potato head was my favorite as well. I can appreciate a cynic.
Do you really think woody knocking buzz out of the window was an accident.
I was just about to ask you the same thing! I really think that it was an accident. Woody is not a villain.
But he did feel pretty left out.
I think that's understandable since he felt like he was being replaced.
But the other toys probably felt the same with woody.
Probably. I thought the scene where the neighbor Sid ends up getting the toys was pretty intense. What did you think?
I appreciated the escape scene with the rocket.
I liked when Buzz and Woody started to become friends and help each other.
Yeah, once they started working together it changed a lot.
What was your favorite friendship moment between Buzz and Woody?
Oh I suppose the reconnaissance mission.
Yours?
I liked that part and how at the end of that scene they found out that Andy got a puppy for Christmas
I guess that part didn't stick out in my mind.
